295.2	Noam_Chomsky	Noam Chomsky	Avram Noam Chomsky in the Department of Linguistics &amp; Philosophy at MIT, where he has worked for over 50 years. Chomsky has been described as the "father of modern linguistics" and a major figure of analytic philosophy. His work has influenced fields such as computer science, mathematics, and psychology.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Chomsky.jpg/230px-Chomsky.jpg
